-- Kremlin economic adviser sees Russia's 2014 GDP growth at 1 pct
-- By Daria Korsunskaya
-- Wed Jul 23, 2014 07:38AM EDT
-- None



MOSCOW, July 23 (Reuters) - Kremlin economic adviser Andrei Belousov said on Monday that Russia's growth domestic product growth is likely to come in at 1 percent this year.

The Economy Ministry's forecasts envisages GDP growth at 0.5 percent but it has said recently that growth may be closer to 1 percent.